Israel â€™s  TA-25 index  declined the
most in more than a week, falling 1.2 percent to 1,148.28 at the
4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 736 million
shekels ($196 million) of shares and convertible securities,
according to bourse data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ampal-American Israel (AMPL)  Corp slumped 19 percent to
0.775 shekel, the lowest close since Bloomberg began tracking
the stock in August 2006. Ampal, owner of 12.5 percent of East
Mediterranean Gas Co., said it had been advised by EMG that
Egyptian General Petroleum Corp. and the Egyptian Natural Gas
Holding Co. were terminating the gas-supply agreement.  A-Online Capital AOC Ltd. (AOC)   surged the most since
June 2004, rallying 20 percent to 0.30 shekel. The financial
markets software maker agreed to buy Harel Finance Trade &
Securities Ltd. from  Harel Insurance Investments & Financial
Services Ltd. (HARL)   for about 84 million shekels. Harel
Insurance dropped 1.7 percent, the most since April 15, to
139.90 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
